modules.description: This module implements POSIX message queues for inter-process communication, supporting operations to open, send, receive, and manage message queues with specific attributes and priorities. It works with message queues identified by names following a strict naming convention, handling messages with payloads and priority levels, and queue attributes like maximum message count and size. Concrete use cases include coordinating data transfer between processes with guaranteed message ordering and prioritization, such as task scheduling or event notification systems.
